President Trump spoke in the Oval Office to announce his plans to strengthen the Buy American principle for federal infrastructure and federal spending. He highlighted the revival of American manufacturing and the increase in manufacturing employment. He emphasized the importance of buying American-made products and reducing reliance on foreign goods. The President also discussed the steel industry and the need for steel in the country. He mentioned the upcoming trade negotiations with China and the progress being made with North Korea. On the topic of the border wall, he stated that without a wall, the country will be unsafe and vulnerable to drugs and human trafficking. He reaffirmed his commitment to building the wall and criticized the Democrats for not supporting it. The President also mentioned the possibility of declaring a national emergency to secure funding for the wall.